The paper discusses recent research advances in Computer Vision and Natural Language Processing, specifically in the task of Visual Question Answering (VQA). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). However, since VQA involves both visual and textual elements, it is also likely to belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses approaches that aim to improve the VQA predictive accuracy, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
